
[1]significant

   SIGNIF'ICANT, a. [L. signigicans.]

   1. Expressive of something beyond the external mark.

   2. Bearing a meaning; expressing or containing signification of sense;
   as a significant word or sound; a significant look.

   3. Betokening something; standing as a sign of something. It was well
   said of Plotinus, that the stars were significant, but not efficient.

   4. Expressive or representative of some fact or event, The passover
   among the Jews was significant of the escape of the Israelites from the
   destruction which fell on the Egyptians. The bread and wine in the
   sacrament are significant of the body and blood of Christ.

   5. Important; momentous. [Not in use.]
